  <TITLE>Update installation terms (&quot;MSSQL&quot; and &quot;SQL Server&quot;)</TITLE>
  <DESCRIPTION>Right now we have the following text on the installation page: &quot;Use SQL Server (or SQL Express) database&quot;. But many hosting companies use the following terms - &quot;MSSQL&quot; or &quot;Microsoft SQL Server&quot;. It can confusing some users. So let's rename it to &quot;Use Microsoft SQL Server (or SQL Express) database&quot;. Do it for all languages in \App_Data\Localization\Installation\installation.en.xml (locale name is &quot;SqlStandard&quot;) P.S. This task will be helpful for non technical users</DESCRIPTION>
  <REPONAME>nopCommerce</REPONAME>
  <TIMEDIFFERENCEDAYS>144</TIMEDIFFERENCEDAYS>
  <BUGGYCOMMIT>
    <MESSAGE>Do not ignore email in GDPR when UsernamesEnabled (#4074) #4074 When UsernamesEnabled, the registration form still asks for email. This means that the email is collected info regardless of UsernamesEnabled. The GDPR requires exporting *all* information related to the user, so this must also be exported regardless of the UsernamesEnabled setting.</MESSAGE>
    <SHA>7589d4cb436ab29c431ab748c239fcedeff12aae</SHA>
